<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-1"></div>
    <div class="col-sm-10" style="margin-top:35px;margin-bottom:35px;">
        <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-3 g-4">
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100" id="hov">
                    <img src="~/contant/images/bft6.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." />
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">👉Live Classes</h5>
                        <p class="card-text" style="text-align:justify">
                            Live classes are an instructor-led learning model where the teacher has control of the class. They decide the learning objective and set the pace of learning. They allow synced events organized in a live virtual classroom where students and teachers meet to study. Online Classes are a combination of video recordings and live lectures with course reading and tests.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100" id="hov">
                    <img src="~/contant/images/bft4.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." />
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">👉Extra and Doubt Classes</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            The Objective of Doubt Discussion Classes is to provide additional attention and care to the students. It helps those students who couldn’t understand a concept at first which is now affecting their performance. It also helps those students who hesitate to ask/discuss their doubts in the classroom because of their shyness and their past academic environment. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100" id="hov">
                    <img src="~/contant/images/bft5.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">👉Special Classes for Week Student</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            Help Weak students to complete the subject related assignments time (initially focus should be to develop habit of work completion on time ,leter on focus should be on correct writing and learing as soon as weak student gain confidence) Weak students will have special classes. Pending work on daliy basis create pressure. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100" id="hov">
                    <img src="~/contant/images/bft3.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">👉To Provide Study Mateial and Course Content</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            Course content is the topics and materials covered in a course. It typically includes a course description, objectives, learning outcomes, and a syllabus. Factual course content includes types of content that focus on facts and data. This can consist of types of course content like lectures, where instructors teach about a certain topic by sharing information with students. 
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100" id="hov">
                    <img src="~/contant/images/bft2.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." />
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">👉Quick Concept Revision & Notes</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            Quick notes help students to revise the whole syllabus in minutes & Seconds. The Key Notes clearly give you a short overview of the complete chapter as these chapter-wise key points are prepared in such a manner that each and every concept from the syllabus is covered in form of Revision Notes. Short Notes are very supportive for last-minute for quick revision of the syllabus. It contains infographics that make it easy to understand.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col">
                <div class="card h-100" id="hov">
                    <img src="~/contant/images/bft1.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." />
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h5 class="card-title">👉Conceptual and Advance Level Tests</h5>
                        <p class="card-text">
                            Concept tests (or ConcepTests) are short, informal, targeted tests that are administered during class to help instructors gauge whether students understand key concepts. They can be used both to assess students' prior knowledge (coming into a course or unit) or their understanding of content in the current course brief, objectives tests are written tests that require the learner to select the correct answer of simple calculations. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-1"></div>
</div>
